<TITLE> DMP makes inroad into city carjacking gang </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Jan 16 (bdnews24.com)  Dhaka Metropolitan Police's Detective Branch apprehended five members of an organised carjacking syndicate in the capital on Saturday. A top DMP official said the syndicate, run by Mohammadpur crime boss Picchi Helal, has been hijacking private vehicles, running drugs in them and working as "hired assassins" for many years. M Mokhlesur Rahman, DMP assistant commissioner, told a press conference that the gang and Picchi Helal had a very influential "godfather". "The police are working to apprehend him," said Rahman. He said the law enforcers, during the arrests, recovered seven stolen private cars, one motorcycle and two foreign handguns along with 12 rounds of ammunition. Two of the five arrestees, identified as Al Shahriar Shuvo, 21, Kabir Khan, 20, and M Anwar Hossain, 20, were arrested from Indira Road. The two handguns were recovered from Shuvo. The two other gang members, Rasheduzzaman Parvez, 26, and Humayun Kabir Pramanik, 30, was arrested from Jatrabari and Shahjahan Road. Rahman said the vehicles were recovered from various locations in the city on information from the arrestees. bd
